## 🧠 Decision Point Example (From v1.2 Upgrade Docs):

**Scenario:** After successful AF_XDP packet handling verification, you should decide whether to inject network partition on MCR channels or keep system running normally for testing multi-channel routing resilience.

```typescript
// TypeScript Interface Effect from upgrade docs: State Mutation Contract  
{ type: 'PARTITION', disabledChannels?: string[] }  // Disable MCR spray on specified channel interfaces  

# Rust struct mutation via Arc<T> (zero-copy shallow clone, no heap alloc)  
struct PartitionNetwork { pub channels: Vec<String> }
impl LabState { 
    pub fn inject_network_partition(&self, channels: &[String]) -> &Self {        
        // extend_from_slice avoids reallocation when capacity exists per consolidated build plan specs         
        let mut state = self.clone();       
            
            for channel in channels.iter() {          
                if !state.network_partitions.contains(channel) {            
                    state.network_partitions.push((*channel).clone());         
                }
            }              
                
    return &mut state;    
}  
}  

# Example payload to inject network partition on MCR spray channels - simpleModeHint enabled per chapter config from Phase 2 MVP deliverable.  
```

